    <!-- ============ S8: COMMON PROBLEMS → HOW WE SOLVE ============ -->
    <section class="sec sec--w" aria-labelledby="s8-h2">
      <div class="ctr">
        <div class="shd rv">
          <span class="srl">Sourcing Comparison</span>
          <h2 class="sh2" id="s8-h2">Six problems sourcing directors keep flagging &mdash; and how our setup answers each.</h2>
          <p class="ssu">Not a knock on other factories &mdash; this is what we made public. Compare row-for-row against your shortlist scorecard.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cp rv">
          <div class="cp__head">
            <div>Problem</div>
            <div>Industry Standard</div>
            <div>Berun</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cp__row">
            <div class="cp__row-h"><i class="bi bi-rulers"></i><span>Tolerance enforcement</span></div>
            <div class="cp__row-i">Tolerance numbers live inside the MSA, not on the website. You see them after you&rsquo;ve already signed.</div>
            <div class="cp__row-b"><strong>&plusmn;5% GSM, &Delta;E &le;1.5, &plusmn;0.5&nbsp;cm</strong> &mdash; printed on this page, written into every PO, attached as report per shipment.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cp__row">
            <div class="cp__row-h"><i class="bi bi-calculator"></i><span>MOQ math</span></div>
            <div class="cp__row-i">MOQ 300 / SKU often reads as 300 &times; 5 sizes = 1,500 unit minimum once your size curve splits.</div>
            <div class="cp__row-b">MOQ 300 is the <strong>total piece count</strong>. Split XS&ndash;XXL however your size curve actually sells. Real number for a 5 SKU pilot: <strong>1,500 total, not 7,500</strong>.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cp__row">
            <div class="cp__row-h"><i class="bi bi-box-seam"></i><span>Sampling start</span></div>
            <div class="cp__row-i">Sample fee plus a 5&ndash;10 piece minimum to even open a sample order.</div>
            <div class="cp__row-b"><strong>One piece per sample. USD&nbsp;45 fee. 5 working days</strong> on fabric-on-stock styles. No bulk commitment required.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cp__row">
            <div class="cp__row-h"><i class="bi bi-hourglass-split"></i><span>On-time delivery accountability</span></div>
            <div class="cp__row-i">OTD% lives in the contract; you find out it slipped after the second late PO.</div>
            <div class="cp__row-b"><strong>12-month rolling OTD 92.4%.</strong> Shipment schedule logs, packing records and delay notes reviewable under NDA for active buyers.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cp__row">
            <div class="cp__row-h"><i class="bi bi-building"></i><span>Single-site vs subcontracted</span></div>
            <div class="cp__row-i">&ldquo;Factory&rdquo; often subcontracts 40&ndash;60% of PO to third-party workshops with no QC alignment &mdash; you find out from inconsistent batches.</div>
            <div class="cp__row-b"><strong>Single 8,500&nbsp;m² site, 280 staff in-house.</strong> No offsite subcontracting. All 12 production lines under one roof, one QC team.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cp__row">
            <div class="cp__row-h"><i class="bi bi-eyedropper"></i><span>Batch-to-batch color consistency</span></div>
            <div class="cp__row-i">Reorder 6 months later, &Delta;E drift averages 2.5&ndash;3.0 &mdash; color visibly doesn&rsquo;t match.</div>
            <div class="cp__row-b"><strong>Spectrophotometer &Delta;E &le;1.5</strong> enforced batch-to-batch. Lab dip approved once, locked into PO master file, audited every reorder.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============ S9: SOURCING PROCESS STEPPER ============ -->
    <section class="sec sec--t" aria-labelledby="s9-h2">
      <div class="ctr">
        <div class="shd rv">
          <span class="srl">Sourcing Process</span>
          <h2 class="sh2" id="s9-h2">From first email to delivered cartons &mdash; five steps over 50 to 58 days.</h2>
          <p class="ssu">We welcome first-time overseas sourcing. No tech-pack? Step&nbsp;1 covers that. We name what we do and what you do at every stage &mdash; no jargon.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ps">
          <div class="ps__n rv">
            <div class="ps__b">1</div>
            <h3 class="ps__t">Inquiry</h3>
            <div class="ps__day">Day 0&ndash;3</div>
            <div class="ps__im"><img src="/assets/images/pattern-sample-approval.webp" alt="Tech-pack document, RFQ printout and reference garment on desk" width="400" height="300" loading="lazy"></div>
            <ul class="ps__list">
              <li><strong>You send</strong>Spec / tech-pack OR reference sample</li>
              <li><strong>We return</strong>RFQ with MOQ, lead time, sample fee, fabric options</li>
              <li><strong>Price</strong>Free, no obligation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="ps__n rv">
            <div class="ps__b">2</div>
            <h3 class="ps__t">Sample</h3>
            <div class="ps__day">Day 4&ndash;9 / 4&ndash;16</div>
