    <!-- ============ S12: CLIENT VOICE — 3 Quote Cards ============ -->
    <section class="sec sec--w" aria-labelledby="s12-h2">
      <div class="ctr">
        <div class="shd rv">
          <span class="srl">Client Voice</span>
          <h2 class="sh2" id="s12-h2">What sourcing-side counterparts say after PO 3.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="qc">
          <div class="qc__c rv">
            <div class="qc__mark">&ldquo;</div>
            <p class="qc__tx">Two factories ago, batch-to-batch GSM drift was killing my Amazon BSR &mdash; 14% variance across one PO. We switched 3 SKUs to Berun. First PO: 4,200 pieces across 4 colors, OTD 17 days, lab dip passed on the first round. Reordered 11K pieces 6 weeks later. The pre-shipment AQL report comes with every PO &mdash; I cut my third-party inspection budget in half.</p>
            <p class="qc__at"><strong>Maya R.</strong> &middot; Senior Sourcing Director<br>Boulder CO athleisure brand ($18M ARR)</p>
            <div class="qc__im"><img src="/assets/images/product-training-performance.webp" alt="4-color performance leggings finished stack on warehouse shelf" width="600" height="450" loading="lazy"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="qc__c rv">
            <div class="qc__mark">&ldquo;</div>
            <p class="qc__tx">Most factories quote MOQ 300 per SKU but actually mean 300 &times; 5 sizes = 1,500 units. That math killed 6 SKU launches for us in 2023. Berun split 300 across XS&ndash;XXL on our first PO &mdash; we launched 5 SKUs in Q1 2024 and hit 88% sell-through within 60 days. They send a monthly OTD report unprompted; I forward it to my CFO every month.</p>
            <p class="qc__at"><strong>Lukas H.</strong> &middot; Brand Founder<br>Berlin EU DTC athleisure ($3.8M ARR)</p>
            <div class="qc__im"><img src="/assets/images/product-athleisure.webp" alt="5-color DTC tee flat-lay showing size split XS-XXL" width="600" height="450" loading="lazy"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="qc__c rv">
            <div class="qc__mark">&ldquo;</div>
            <p class="qc__tx">Annual trainer uniform reorder is non-negotiable &mdash; if last year&rsquo;s batch and this year&rsquo;s batch don&rsquo;t match in person, members ask why. Berun&rsquo;s &Delta;E drift has stayed under 1.0 across three reorder years. We sized the new locations in year 4 and the spectrophotometer log proves the color is identical to year 1. No batch-to-batch surprises means I don&rsquo;t carry safety stock for color compensation.</p>
            <p class="qc__at"><strong>Tate W.</strong> &middot; Operations Director<br>12-location Atlanta GA gym chain</p>
            <div class="qc__im"><img src="https://app.grapesjs.com/api/assets/random-image?query=3-trainer-uniforms-hung-side-by-side-color-match-across-years&w=600&h=450&seed=qc03" alt="3 trainer uniforms hung side-by-side showing color match across years" width="600" height="450" loading="lazy"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

