    <!-- ============ S14: FAQ ============ -->
    <section class="sec sec--w" aria-labelledby="s14-h2">
      <div class="ctr">
        <div class="shd rv">
          <span class="srl">FAQ</span>
          <h2 class="sh2" id="s14-h2">Eight questions sourcing directors and first-time founders ask before PO 1.</h2>
          <p class="ssu">Sourcing-side jargon translated in the answers. Link to the relevant section if you want depth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq__lead rv">
          <img src="https://app.grapesjs.com/api/assets/random-image?query=sourcing-director-and-factory-rep-reviewing-tech-pack-documents-at-office-desk-friendly-professional&w=1200&h=525&seed=faq01" alt="Sourcing director and Berun rep reviewing tech-pack documents at factory office desk" width="1200" height="525" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="faq">
          <details class="faq__i">
            <summary class="faq__q">How is MOQ split across sizes? Does 300 mean 300 per SKU or 300 &times; 5 sizes?</summary>
            <div class="faq__a">
              <p>Our MOQ 300 is the <strong>total piece count</strong> for one SKU &mdash; not per size. You decide the size curve. If your sales data says XS=10% / S=20% / M=30% / L=25% / XL=15%, we cut 30/60/90/75/45 pieces. Most factories quote 300 per size, which means 1,500 pieces minimum once your size curve splits. We don&rsquo;t.</p>
              <p><a href="#s5-h2">Production Services Card&nbsp;1 &uarr;</a> &middot; <a href="#s8-h2">Common Problems Row&nbsp;2 &uarr;</a></p>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq__i">
            <summary class="faq__q">What&rsquo;s your sampling cost and turnaround time?</summary>
            <div class="faq__a">
              <p>USD&nbsp;45 per sample. 5 working days on fabric we have in stock; 12 working days if your fabric is custom or sourced. You get a full one-piece sample with pattern + fabric swatch + lab dip color match. No bulk commitment required.</p>
              <p><a href="#s5-h2">Production Services Card&nbsp;4 &uarr;</a></p>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq__i">
            <summary class="faq__q">I don&rsquo;t have a tech-pack &mdash; can I still work with you?</summary>
            <div class="faq__a">
              <p>Yes. Our 16 pattern-makers can build a tech-pack from a reference sample (a garment you already own) or a sketch. The pattern fee is USD&nbsp;220 and it takes 7&ndash;14 days. After that we proceed exactly the same way as a client who brought their own tech-pack.</p>
              <p><a href="#s5-h2">Production Services Card&nbsp;7 &uarr;</a> &middot; <a href="#s9-h2">Sourcing Process Step&nbsp;1 &uarr;</a></p>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq__i">
            <summary class="faq__q">What does AQL 2.5 actually mean for my order?</summary>
            <div class="faq__a">
              <p>AQL stands for <strong>Acceptable Quality Limit</strong> &mdash; it&rsquo;s the inspection sampling rate we use per ANSI/ASQ Z1.4. In plain English: we randomly inspect a statistically valid sample of pieces from your batch (typically 80&ndash;200 pieces depending on PO size) and check for defects. AQL 2.5 is the standard quality level retailers like Target and Costco require. We share the inspection report with every shipment.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq__i">
            <summary class="faq__q">What&rsquo;s your on-time delivery rate? Can I see evidence?</summary>
            <div class="faq__a">
              <p>12-month rolling OTD is <strong>92.4%</strong>. We log every shipment with promised date, actual date, and delay reason. The full log is reviewable under NDA for active buyers. We also send monthly OTD reports to repeat clients without being asked.</p>
              <p><a href="#s6-h2">Capacity Datasheet Row&nbsp;9 &uarr;</a> &middot; <a href="#s8-h2">Common Problems Row&nbsp;4 &uarr;</a></p>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq__i">
            <summary class="faq__q">Difference between OEM, ODM, and Private Label?</summary>
            <div class="faq__a">
              <p><strong>OEM</strong>: you bring the tech-pack and the design &mdash; we cut and sew to your spec. <strong>ODM</strong>: you pick from our pattern library and customize color / fabric / logo &mdash; we skip the pattern-making cycle so you launch faster. <strong>Private Label</strong>: add your hangtag, care label, polybag and master carton on top of OEM or ODM. Private Label has no extra MOQ &mdash; it&rsquo;s an add-on.</p>
              <p><a href="#s5-h2">Production Services Cards&nbsp;1, 2, 3 &uarr;</a></p>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq__i">
            <summary class="faq__q">Payment terms and FOB / CIF options?</summary>
            <div class="faq__a">
              <p>Standard PO terms: <strong>30% deposit</strong> on PO confirmation, <strong>70% balance</strong> on BL (bill of lading) copy. FOB is default (you arrange shipping from our nearest port). CIF available on request (we arrange shipping to your destination port). For active buyers with repeat orders, we offer NET-30 on the balance.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq__i">
            <summary class="faq__q">How do you handle batch-to-batch color consistency?</summary>
            <div class="faq__a">
              <p>Every PO starts with a <strong>lab dip</strong> &mdash; your approved color sample. We measure &Delta;E (color delta) against the lab dip using a spectrophotometer at three checkpoints: fabric receiving, mid-production, and pre-shipment. &Delta;E must stay &le; 1.5. The lab dip is stored in your client master file and pulled for every reorder &mdash; so a reorder 6 months later matches the original.</p>
              <p><a href="#s2-h2">5-Sec Disqualifier Stat&nbsp;2 &uarr;</a></p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
        <p class="faq__foot rv">Have another question? Email <a href="mailto:sales@berunactivewear.com">sales@berunactivewear.com</a> &mdash; we reply within 1 business day.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============ S15: FINAL CTA + FORM ============ -->
    <section class="fc" aria-labelledby="s15-h2">
      <div class="ctr">
        <h2 class="fc__h rv" id="s15-h2">Ready to put a real factory on your shortlist?</h2>
        <p class="fc__s rv">Send your tech-pack and we&rsquo;ll come back within one business day with a per-size MOQ split, sampling timeline, and an FOB quote. Or book a 30-min sourcing call with our engineering lead first.</p>
        <div class="fc__form rv">
          <form id="inquiry-form" action="https://form.lianf.com/" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
            <input type="hidden" name="domain" value="berunactivewear.com">
            <input type="hidden" name="page" value="index">
            <input type="text" name="website" style="display:none" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off">
            <div class="fc__fields">
              <div class="fc__field">
                <label for="idx-name">Full Name <span style="color:var(--c1)">*</span></label>
                <input type="text" id="idx-name" name="name" required placeholder="Your full name">
              </div>
              <div class="fc__field">
                <label for="idx-email">Email <span style="color:var(--c1)">*</span></label>
                <input type="email" id="idx-email" name="email" required placeholder="you@company.com">
              </div>
              <div class="fc__field">
                <label for="idx-phone">Phone / WhatsApp</label>
                <input type="tel" id="idx-phone" name="phone" placeholder="+1 555 000 0000">
              </div>
              <div class="fc__field">
                <label for="idx-company">Company / Brand</label>
                <input type="text" id="idx-company" name="company" placeholder="Your brand name">
              </div>
              <div class="fc__field fc__field--full">
                <label for="idx-msg">Project Brief <span style="color:var(--c1)">*</span></label>
                <textarea id="idx-msg" name="message" rows="3" required placeholder="Tell us: product type (leggings / hoodie / team jersey...), quantities per size, fabric preference, target ship date."></textarea>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="fc__b" style="margin:18px 0 6px">
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn--p" style="flex:1;min-width:200px"><i class="bi bi-send" aria-hidden="true"></i> Book a 30-min Sourcing Call</button>
              <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--o"><i class="bi bi-file-earmark-spreadsheet" aria-hidden="true"></i> Download Spec Template (XLSX)</a>
            </div>
          </form>
        </div>
        <p class="fc__tr rv">Replies within 1 business day <span>&middot;</span> NDA on request <span>&middot;</span> Sample fee waived after first PO</p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <div id="footer-container"></div>
  <script src="/assets/footer.js" defer></script>
  <script>window.WhatsAppWidgetConfig={contactsFile:'/assets/whatsapp-contacts.json'};</script>
  <script src="/assets/whatsapp-widget.js" defer></script>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" defer></script>
  <script>
  (function(){
    var els=document.querySelectorAll('.rv');
    if(!els.length)return;
    var io=new IntersectionObserver(function(entries){
      entries.forEach(function(e){if(e.isIntersecting){e.target.classList.add('vis');io.unobserve(e.target)}});
    },{threshold:.12,rootMargin:'0px 0px -40px 0px'});
    els.forEach(function(el){io.observe(el)});
  })();
  </script>
  <script>
  (function(){
    var fallbacks=['factory-production','textile-manufacturing','garment-sewing','fabric-cutting','warehouse-logistics','quality-inspection','industrial-workshop','clothing-production'];
    document.querySelectorAll('main img').forEach(function(img){
      img.onerror=function(){
        var el=this;
        if(el.dataset.retried) {
          var ph=document.createElement('div');
          ph.className='img-ph';
          ph.style.width='100%';
          ph.style.aspectRatio=(el.width&&el.height)?(el.width+'/'+el.height):'4/3';
          ph.innerHTML='<i class="bi bi-camera"></i><span>Photo pending</span>';
          el.replaceWith(ph);
          return;
        }
        el.dataset.retried='1';
        var q=fallbacks[Math.floor(Math.random()*fallbacks.length)];
        var w=el.width||400,h=el.height||300;
        el.src='https://app.grapesjs.com/api/assets/random-image?query='+q+'&w='+w+'&h='+h;
      };
    });
  })();
  </script>
  <script>
  (function(){
    var f=document.querySelector('#inquiry-form');
    if(!f)return;
    var t=Date.now();
    f.addEventListener('submit',function(){
      var s=document.createElement('input');s.type='hidden';s.name='submission_time';s.value=Math.floor((Date.now()-t)/1000);this.appendChild(s);
      var p=document.createElement('input');p.type='hidden';p.name='page_url';p.value=window.location.href;this.appendChild(p);
    });
  })();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
